Aksigorta, Ford Otosan, Sabanci, Turkcell: Turkey Stock Preview

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-07-27T06:44:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/aksigorta-ford-otosan-sabanci-turkcell-turkey-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in  Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 Index (XU100)  rose 0.6 percent
to 61,388.64.  Aksigorta AS (AKGRT)  : Brussels-based  Ageas (AGS)   and
Turkish partner  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)   will
present their plans for the Turkish non-life insurer after Ageas
bought a 31 percent stake from Sabanci in February. Aksigorta
jumped 6 kurus, or 4 percent, to 1.56 liras yesterday.  Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO)  : The maker of Ford
vehicles in Turkey was raised to “neutral” from “sell” at
UBS AG. The shares fell 5 kurus, or 0.4 percent, to 12.45 liras.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
biggest mobile phone company may report net profit of 19.9
million liras, down from a profit of 425 million liras in the
second quarter last year, according to the mean estimate of 11
analysts in a Bloomberg survey, five of whom forecasted a loss.
The shares rose 6 kurus, or 0.7 percent, to 8.66 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
